    "The paper is organized into four main sections: Sect. 2 presents the AI/ML algorithms and discusses their characteristics and applications.",
    "Deep generative models are firstly introduced, namely variational autoencoders, transformers and diffusion models, followed by contrastive methods.",
    "Afterwards, AI/ML algorithms focused on explainability are addressed.",
    "Additional AI/ML techniques are also presented, specifically active learning, semi-supervised learning, weak supervision, zero-shot learning and clustering & dimensionality reduction, along with diverse applications, such as text processing and computer vision.",
    "The Section ends with a discussion about limitations and opportunities involving AI/ML algorithms."
